	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I haven't needed to try doing it myself yet, but I've seen it done.  I'm pretty sure it requires more than one soldering iron (and not a weak one).  It's bad enough desoldering something that's on a ground plane, but when it's a metal box soldered to a ground plane, the heat is not gonna stay where you want it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
